Additionally, the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category as it deals with learning algorithms. The use of second-order information also suggests that it may be relevant to the optimization (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) categories. Finally, the empirical evaluation of the proposed algorithm on real-world datasets suggests that it may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
